{
  "text": "An Elman neural network [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] is a kind of recursive network, which can approximate arbitrarily nonlinear functions with arbitrary precision. For the reason that a new layer is added to the hidden layer of the feed-forward network as a one-step delay operator to achieve memory ability, it has good approximation ability and dynamic characteristics. Additionally, it is well adaptive and self-organizing. Therefore, Elman networks have a wide range of applications, in areas such as function approximation, pattern recognition, and data compression.",
